.TH RUFUSARM64-DEVICE-BACKUP 1 "20 July 2026" "RufusArm64 0.13.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rufusarm64-device-backup \- save a verified image of a removable drive
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rufusarm64-device-backup
.B --device
.I /dev/DEVICE
.B --output
.I /absolute/path/drive.img
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B rufusarm64-device-backup
.B --device
.I /dev/DEVICE
.B --output
.I /absolute/path/drive.img
.B --dry-run
.RI [ --json ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rufusarm64-device-backup
captures the exact reported capacity of one explicitly selected whole block
device into a newly created image file. The source is opened read-only, bound
to its kernel identity and capacity, and revalidated before and after capture.
.PP
The completed image is published atomically only after every byte is copied,
SHA-256 is calculated, the file is synchronized, and source and destination
identities are rechecked. Existing files are never replaced. Incomplete output
is removed after failure or cancellation.
.PP
The destination must have enough available space and reside on a different
physical disk from the selected source. Mounted removable filesystems are
unmounted before capture unless
.B --no-unmount
is supplied.
.SH GRAPHICAL WORKFLOW
Select a removable drive and choose
.BR "Save drive image…" .
RufusArm64 first runs an unprivileged destination plan and displays the exact
source, capacity, destination directory, required bytes, and available bytes.
Before authentication it requires the exact phrase
.B SAVE /dev/DEVICE TO /absolute/path/drive.img .
The dialog reports progress, throughput, ETA, cancellation, final SHA-256, and
the published image path.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --device " /dev/DEVICE"
Select the whole source disk. Partitions and paths outside
.I /dev
are refused.
.TP
.BI --output " PATH"
Absolute path for the new image file. The path must not already exist.
.TP
.BI --expected-identity " TOKEN"
Require the exact identity token returned by
.BR "rufusarm64-cli list --json" .
This is mandatory with
.B --yes
or
.BR --allow-fixed .
.TP
.B --dry-run
Validate source and destination storage without opening the source device.
.TP
.B --json
Emit one deterministic JSON plan or report.
.TP
.B --progress-json
Emit bounded schema-1 progress records on standard error while retaining the
final deterministic report on standard output.
.TP
.B --yes
Skip terminal confirmation. Accepted only with an exact expected identity.
.TP
.B --allow-fixed
Permit a non-removable whole disk for a direct terminal invocation. Root-disk
and protected-mount refusals remain in force.
.TP
.B --no-unmount
Refuse mounted filesystems instead of unmounting eligible removable mounts.
.TP
.BR --version , " -v"
Print the installed version.
.SH SAFETY
The source is never opened for writing, but coherent capture normally requires
its filesystems to be unmounted. No final pathname appears before verified
completion. Manually created image files remain user data after package removal.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rufusarm64 (1),
.BR rufusarm64-cli (1),
.BR rufusarm64-device-qualify (1)
